</p>

<p>(b)
We aim to find the polar form of \(2xy={@bb@}\):
\[
\begin{aligned}
2xy &= {@bb@} \\
2(r\cos\theta)(r\sin\theta) &= {@bb@}\\
r^2\sin2\theta &= {@bb@}\\
r^2 &= \frac{{@bb@}}{\sin2\theta}
\end{aligned}
\]

